BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 210.0 720 Td (Chapter 2: Waking Up) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (One spring morning, rain soaked into the soil around Seedling.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('Oh! Water!' Seedling felt herself swelling up as she soaked it in.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (The water softened her tough seed coat. She could feel herself waking up!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (A tiny white root poked out from the bottom of her shell.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('I am growing!' Seedling cheered. 'I am finally growing!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (The root pushed deeper into the soil, anchoring her in place. Life had begun!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: GERMINATION) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Germination is when a seed starts to grow into a new plant.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Seeds need three things to germinate: water, warmth, and oxygen.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Water soaks into the seed, making it swell and crack open the seed coat.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (The first thing to grow is always the root \(radicle\) - it grows downward.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Then the shoot \(plumule\) pushes upward toward the light and air.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* Some seeds germinate in just 1-2 days; others take weeks or months!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* Bean seeds are great for watching germination - they sprout in about 5 days.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Some seeds need fire, cold, or even animal digestion to trigger germination!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Put a bean seed between wet paper towels in a bag. Watch it sprout over 5 days!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (Why does the root always grow DOWN and the shoot always grow UP?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
