BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 157.20000000000002 720 Td (Chapter 3: Reaching for the Sun) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Seedling's green shoot pushed up through the dark soil with all her might.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (POP! She broke through the surface into the bright, beautiful sunlight!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('The world is so big and bright!' Seedling gasped, seeing the sky for the first time.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (Her tiny stem leaned toward the warm sunshine like a dancer reaching for a spotlight.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (Two little leaves unfurled like tiny green hands reaching toward the light.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('I need that sunlight!' Seedling could feel it. The light was her energy source.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: PHOTOTROPISM) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Phototropism means growing toward light \(photo=light, tropism=turning\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Plants can actually sense where light is coming from and bend toward it!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (A hormone called auxin collects on the shady side, making that side grow faster.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (The shady side growing faster causes the plant to bend toward the light.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (This is why houseplants lean toward windows - they are chasing the sunshine!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* Sunflowers are famous for following the sun across the sky \(when young\)!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* Roots show negative phototropism - they grow AWAY from light, deeper into soil.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Some plants can completely turn their leaves to face the sun during the day.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Put a plant near a window. After a week, see how it leans toward the light. Rotate it and watch!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (What would happen to a plant if it could not sense light at all?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
