BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 147.6 720 Td (Chapter 5: Drinking Through Roots) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (While Seedling's leaves worked above ground, her roots were busy underground.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (They spread out like fingers reaching through the soil in every direction.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('I am so thirsty!' Seedling said. 'My roots need to find water!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (Tiny root hairs, thinner than human hair, absorbed water like tiny sponges.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (The water traveled up through the stem like drinking through a straw.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('All the way from my roots to my highest leaf!' Seedling marveled at herself.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: ROOT SYSTEMS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Roots have two main jobs: anchoring the plant in soil and absorbing water and minerals.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Root hairs are tiny extensions that greatly increase the surface area for absorption.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Water moves from soil into roots through osmosis \(water moves toward higher concentration\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Some trees have roots that spread wider underground than the tree's branches above!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Water travels up through tiny tubes \(xylem\) against gravity using capillary action.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* A single rye grass plant can have 14 billion root hairs!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* The deepest known root belongs to a fig tree - over 400 feet deep!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Roots can sense water and grow toward it - this is called hydrotropism.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Put a white flower \(carnation\) in colored water. Watch the color travel up the stem!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (How does water get from the roots to the top of a 300-foot tall tree?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
