BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 162.0 720 Td (Chapter 6: Flowers and Friends) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (After many seasons of growing, something wonderful happened to Seedling.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (Beautiful flowers bloomed on her branches for the very first time!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('Why am I making flowers?' Seedling wondered. 'They are so pretty!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (BUZZ! A fuzzy bumblebee landed on one of her flowers, covered in yellow dust.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('Thank you for the sweet nectar!' the bee said, flying to another flower.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('That bee is helping me make seeds!' Seedling realized. 'We are a team!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: POLLINATION) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Flowers are not just pretty - they are a plant's way of making new plants!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Pollen is a yellow powder made by the male part of the flower \(stamen\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Pollination happens when pollen reaches the female part \(pistil\) of another flower.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Bees, butterflies, birds, bats, and even wind carry pollen between flowers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Flowers attract pollinators with bright colors, sweet scent, and tasty nectar.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* Bees pollinate about 75% of the fruits and vegetables we eat!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* Some flowers only bloom at night to attract moth and bat pollinators.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Without pollinators, we would lose most of our food crops!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Look closely at a flower. Can you find the stamen \(pollen\) and pistil \(center\)? Use a magnifier!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (Why are so many flowers brightly colored? Who are they trying to attract?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
