BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 176.4 720 Td (Chapter 7: Fruits and Seeds) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (After the bees did their work, Seedling's flowers changed into something new.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (Where each flower had been, a fruit began to grow - with seeds inside!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('My babies!' Seedling said proudly, looking at her acorns \(oak tree fruits\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (A squirrel came and took some acorns, burying them in the ground far away.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (The wind blew some seeds to new places. A bird ate a berry and flew off.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('My children will grow in new places all over the forest!' Seedling was so happy.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: SEED DISPERSAL) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (After pollination, flowers develop into fruits that contain seeds.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Seeds need to travel away from the parent plant to find space and sunlight.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Wind dispersal: Dandelion seeds have 'parachutes,' maple seeds have 'helicopters.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Animal dispersal: Birds eat berries and drop seeds far away in their droppings.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Water dispersal: Coconuts float across oceans to reach new islands!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* Dandelion seeds can travel up to 5 miles on the wind!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* Every fruit you eat started as a flower - apples, oranges, even tomatoes!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Some seeds \(like burrs\) have tiny hooks that stick to animal fur for a free ride.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Collect different seeds. Sort them by how they travel: wind, animal, water, or explosion!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (Why is it important that seeds travel far from the parent plant?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
