BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 190.8 720 Td (Chapter 8: A Mighty Tree) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Years passed. Seasons came and went. Seedling grew taller every year.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (She was no longer a tiny seedling - she was now a magnificent oak tree!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (Birds built nests in her branches. Squirrels stored acorns in her trunk.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (Children played in her shade on hot summer days.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('I started as a tiny seed no bigger than a marble,' she remembered.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('And now look at me! Patience and persistence helped me grow into something great!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: TREE RINGS AND GROWTH) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Trees grow a new layer of wood each year, creating visible rings in the trunk.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (You can count a tree's rings to discover its age - one ring per year!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Wide rings mean a good year with plenty of rain; thin rings mean drought.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (The oldest living tree is over 5,000 years old \(a bristlecone pine in California\)!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Trees produce oxygen, clean the air, provide habitat, and prevent soil erosion.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 14 Tf 72 444 Td (MORAL:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F5 13 Tf 72 424 Td (Great things start small - patience and persistence make you grow!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 335 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 394 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 374 Td (* A single oak tree can produce 70,000 acorns in one year!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 356 Td (* Trees communicate underground through a 'wood wide web' of fungal networks.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 338 Td (* The tallest tree in the world is a redwood named Hyperion - 380 feet tall!) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
